<h3><a name="5">5. Samarithan</a></h3><br />
One day I saw a man<br />
dressed in rags, with a staff in his hand<br />
begging for a penny to survive<br />
How poor a man can be<br />
I gave him hospitality<br />
a room, a bed and lots of food to eat<br />
Still I hear his last few words<br />
"I can never return what you've done<br />
heaven will remember and repay"<br />
<br />
Fifty years had gone since I saw him<br />
I was dying and I'd soon be dead<br />
Three angels stood in front of me bed<br />
The first one she said to me, don't be afraid<br />
<br />
I will give you immortality, and grace for your soul<br />
The second had eyes of gold, she gave me my wings<br />
The third gave all wisdom, and angel could give<br />
...to me<br />
