I sleep by your shadow<br />
remembering your light<br />
In my heart<br />
I'm with you every night<br />
Far goes your journey<br />
into the unknown<br />
wherever you might be<br />
be well my son <i>[1st Time: you are my son]</i><br />
Why just you my flesh and blood<br />
I cannot live nor understand<br />
my dearest treasure to be found<br />
six feet under in sacred ground<br />
Watch me bleed you lucky ones<br />
I envy you your living sons<br />
I'll give mine the strength of my faithful breath<br />
I will mourn him to my death<br />
